In a food processor blend goat cheese, cream, paprika, caraway seeds, mustard, garlic, anchovies, and salt and pepper to taste until smooth.
Transfer mixture to a bowl and stir in scallions and capers. Chill spread, covered, at least 2 hours and up to 2 weeks. Serve as a dip for crudité or as a spread for crackers or sandwiches. Makes about 2 1/2 cups.
